01:55:39.960 --> 01:55:42.200
So maybe a last question.

01:55:42.200 --> 01:55:43.600
When we talked a little bit before,

01:55:43.600 --> 01:55:48.280
you're talking about immigration reform under Reagan.

01:55:48.280 --> 01:55:51.360
Can you talk a little bit about where we are now

01:55:51.360 --> 01:55:56.960
and your thoughts on especially immigration issues?

01:55:56.960 --> 01:56:04.200
Well, the United States, although it's a country of immigrants,

01:56:04.200 --> 01:56:08.360
the only native native Americans in the Piederns

01:56:08.360 --> 01:56:10.000
were immigrants.

01:56:10.000 --> 01:56:13.320
As a matter of fact, the Spaniards, the Spanish,

01:56:13.320 --> 01:56:16.320
were here over 100 years before the Piederns arrived.

01:56:16.320 --> 01:56:19.560
And other immigrants from other countries,

01:56:19.560 --> 01:56:24.480
all over the world have come to this country.

01:56:24.480 --> 01:56:26.280
We're a country of immigrants.

01:56:26.280 --> 01:56:27.520
And we're proud out of it.

01:56:27.520 --> 01:56:30.640
As a matter of fact, our constitution

01:56:30.640 --> 01:56:35.080
spills out that we're all equal under the law.

01:56:35.080 --> 01:56:37.040
And we all participate.

01:56:37.040 --> 01:56:40.280
As a matter of fact, the French donated a statue

01:56:40.280 --> 01:56:43.920
welcoming immigrants to this country.

01:56:43.920 --> 01:56:50.280
Whether it be Irish from escaping the potato famine,

01:56:50.280 --> 01:56:56.880
be the Italians, be the Irish, be the from South

01:56:56.880 --> 01:56:59.920
and Central America, be the from Asia,

01:56:59.920 --> 01:57:03.080
we're a country of immigrants.

01:57:03.080 --> 01:57:04.680
That's our history.

01:57:04.680 --> 01:57:06.640
That's what made this country great.

01:57:06.640 --> 01:57:11.480
However, it's also a dynamic issue.

01:57:11.520 --> 01:57:15.720
And things have changed over the years,

01:57:15.720 --> 01:57:20.120
whereby it was open borders and welcoming everybody

01:57:20.120 --> 01:57:23.240
to being in a little bit concerned that maybe they're

01:57:23.240 --> 01:57:25.600
taking jobs away.

01:57:25.600 --> 01:57:30.320
And nobody paid attention to the jobs they took

01:57:30.320 --> 01:57:35.080
or they got, where jobs that people didn't want.

01:57:35.080 --> 01:57:38.960
My first wife is from Oregon.

01:57:38.960 --> 01:57:43.520
The few workers that were available to work

01:57:43.520 --> 01:57:47.480
in the Willamette Valley and the Farms were immigrants

01:57:47.480 --> 01:57:48.200
from Mexico.

01:57:51.160 --> 01:57:53.000
Yet there were not enough immigrants.

01:57:53.000 --> 01:57:56.280
You had strawberries rotting in the fields

01:57:56.280 --> 01:57:57.840
because they were not enough.

01:57:57.840 --> 01:58:01.320
As a matter of fact, the schools closed early.

01:58:01.320 --> 01:58:05.000
So the children could go out in the fields and pick strawberries.

01:58:05.000 --> 01:58:07.280
So they wouldn't be rotting in the fields.

01:58:09.120 --> 01:58:14.040
People don't realize that they're creating jobs.

01:58:14.040 --> 01:58:16.240
Immigrants are creating jobs.

01:58:16.240 --> 01:58:22.920
They just think, sure, that over 80% of the farm work

01:58:22.920 --> 01:58:26.360
in California is then by immigrants.

01:58:31.640 --> 01:58:37.600
The Immigration Reform and Control Act that we did is to pardon those who are already

01:58:37.600 --> 01:58:39.840
here.

01:58:39.840 --> 01:58:48.040
Yes, I agree that there should be a regulated process

01:58:48.040 --> 01:58:52.080
to how people come here and so forth.

01:58:52.080 --> 01:58:55.960
But because we are immigrant.

01:58:55.960 --> 01:59:00.040
As a matter of fact, research has shown

01:59:00.040 --> 01:59:04.880
that immigrants contribute billions of dollars

01:59:04.880 --> 01:59:12.480
to our economy and have invented developments

01:59:12.480 --> 01:59:17.800
in our high-tech world and contributed significantly.

01:59:17.800 --> 01:59:24.040
But yet they persist this concern, that A, they're taking jobs.

01:59:24.040 --> 01:59:28.440
And now more recently, since we got involved in wars

01:59:28.440 --> 01:59:33.000
in the Middle East, that there are people

01:59:33.000 --> 01:59:36.800
that have hostile feelings are coming here

01:59:36.800 --> 01:59:44.520
with that hostility from countries from Iran, Iraq,

01:59:44.520 --> 01:59:49.360
other Saudi Arabia, other countries that may not

01:59:49.360 --> 01:59:51.720
have friendly intentions.

01:59:51.720 --> 01:59:58.640
That dimension adds to the mix of sentiment about immigrants.

01:59:58.640 --> 02:00:01.200
As a matter of fact, one candidate, the Schrodinger

02:00:01.200 --> 02:00:06.640
for President, is talking about building walls and deporting.

02:00:06.640 --> 02:00:07.840
It's a debate.

02:00:07.840 --> 02:00:11.720
It's an ongoing, fluctuating debate.

02:00:11.720 --> 02:00:16.800
But my opinion is that we're a country of immigrants.

02:00:16.800 --> 02:00:24.160
Yes, it makes sense that we should have a regulated process

02:00:24.160 --> 02:00:28.720
so that it's a control to the extent that it's

02:00:28.720 --> 02:00:35.800
absorbed, that's as needed by our economy, by our communities.

02:00:35.800 --> 02:00:38.840
But we don't put walls.

02:00:38.840 --> 02:00:45.680
That's not the reasonable, sensible way to purchase.

02:00:45.680 --> 02:00:50.080
But yes, we should have some kind of regulated process

02:00:50.080 --> 02:00:56.800
that we all have a voice to say about having the same policy

02:00:56.800 --> 02:01:01.680
on how we manage that.

02:01:01.680 --> 02:01:02.920
Thank you.

